criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  recurrent low back pain in the last three months;

          -  medical diagnosis of non-specific low back pain, daily or almost daily;

          -  subjects that will present at least four variables which encompass the clinical
             prediction rule: symptoms duration less than 16 days, Fear Avoidance-Beliefs
             Questionnaire score lower than 19 in the work subscale, segmental lumbar hypermobility
             test in prone decubitus, internal hip rotation higher than 35 degrees and symptoms
             that don't pass the knee.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  subjects presenting symptoms that pass the knee;

          -  impairment of neurologic signs like sensibility, muscle force and deep tendon reflex;

          -  a prior history of spondylolisthesis, spinal stenosis, inflammatory disease, cancer,
             musculoskeletal degenerative disease, pregnancy, disease and drugs that impairment the
             balance;

          -  subjects who received a HVLA manipulation of the lumbar spine at least three months
             earlier;

          -  will be excluded women older than 50 years, that don't will present a bone mineral
             density exam.
